'''Mehdi Taremi'''{{Efn-lr|{{langx|fa|مهدی طارمی}}, {{IPA|fa|mæhˈdiː tʰɒːɹeˈmiː|IPA}}}} (born 18 July 1992) is an Iranian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[striker (association football)|striker]] for [[Super League Greece]] club [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] and the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]].

A [[late bloomer]], he began his career at [[Shahin Bushehr F.C.|Shahin Bushehr]] and [[Iranjavan F.C.|Iranjavan]], and then played for [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] between 2014 and 2018; he was [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] top scorer on two occasions (2015–16 and 2016–17). He played for Qatari side [[Al-Gharafa Sports Club|Al-Gharafa]] between 2018 and 2019, before joining [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] in Portugal, with whom he was [[Primeira Liga]] joint-top scorer in [[2019–20 Primeira Liga|2019–20]]. In 2020, he moved to fellow Portuguese side [[FC Porto]] and won the domestic double in [[2021–22 Primeira Liga|2021–22]]. He went on to continue this success in the [[2022–23 Primeira Liga|2022–23]] season by finishing as the top goal scorer in the league and winning a domestic cup double of [[Taça de Portugal]] and [[Taça da Liga]]. After a short spell at [[Inter Milan]], with which he reached the [[2025 UEFA Champions League final]], he signed for Greek powerhouse [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]].

Taremi made his first senior appearance in 2015, and represented Iran at the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]] and [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]], and the [[AFC Asian Cup]] in [[2019 AFC Asian Cup|2019]] and [[2023 AFC Asian Cup|2023]].

== Early life and family ==
Mehdi Taremi was born on 18 July 1992 in [[Bushehr]], Iran. He is the third and youngest child of his family. His father Alishah Taremi was an amateur footballer who played in local leagues.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|title=Getting to Know the Iranian National Team: Mehdi Taremi|url=https://iranwire.com/en/sports/107461-getting-to-know-the-iranian-national-team-mehdi-taremi/|website=[[IranWire]]|access-date=2025-11-27|language=en}}</ref> His older brother Mohammad is also a football player.<ref>{{Cite web |title=روایت برادر آقای گل از شب تلخ خانواده طارمی|url=https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1454709|publisher=[[Varzesh 3]]|language=fa|access-date=23 July 2022|archive-date=24 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220924085016/https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1454709/%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%93%D9%82%D8%A7%DB%8C-%DA%AF%D9%84-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%B4%D8%A8-%D8%AA%D9%84%D8%AE-%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Taremi started his career with Bargh Bushehr's Academy before moving on to [[Iranjavan F.C.|Iranjavan]]'s Youth Academy.<ref>{{cite web|title=فوتبالیست بوشهری به تیم پرسپولیس تهران پیوست – Tasnim|url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1393/03/01/376848|language=fa|access-date=9 January 2018|archive-date=24 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220924084901/https://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1393/03/01/376848|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Shahin Bushehr===
Taremi joined [[Shahin Bushehr F.C.|Shahin Bushehr]] in the summer of 2010. He played seven games and scored one goal in all competitions. In the winter of 2012, he was released by [[Shahin Bushehr F.C.|Shahin Bushehr]] to spend his conscription period in a military club, but he failed to join a club and was forced to spend his conscription period in a usual garrison.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ptfbu.ir/6006//News/%DA%AF%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B4-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B2/ |title=PTFBU.IR – Biography |access-date=30 May 2014 |archive-date=7 February 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160207175909/http://ptfbu.ir/6006//News/%DA%AF%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B4-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B2/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Iranjavan===
Taremi joined [[Iranjavan F.C.|Iranjavan]] in the summer of 2013 and signed a two-year contract until the end of the 2014–15 season and was given the number 9. Taremi scored 12 times in 22 matches in [[2013–14 Azadegan League|2013–14]], and became the league's second top scorer after Mokhtar Jomehzadeh.

===Persepolis===
[[File:Mehdi Taremi in training.jpg|left|thumb|Taremi in [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] training in 2016|180px]]
After becoming the [[Azadegan League]]'s top scorer, Taremi had offers from many teams. He joined [[Perspolis F.C.|Persepolis]] in the summer of 2014 and signed a two-year contract through June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=طارمی با پرسپولیس قرارداد داخلی بست :: ورزش سه|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news.do?itemid=1106060&title=%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%D9%8A_%D8%A8%D8%A7_%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%BE%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%B3_%D9%82%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF_%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%84%D9%8A_%D8%A8%D8%B3%D8%AA|website=www.varzesh3.com}}</ref>

====2014–15====
Taremi made his debut in 1–1 draw with [[Naft Tehran F.C.|Naft Tehran]], coming as a substitute for [[Reza Norouzi]] in 90th minute. He scored his first goal for the club on 15 August 2014 in a 1–0 victory over [[Zob Ahan F.C.|Zob Ahan]]. On 8 April 2015 Taremi scored a penalty in [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] 1–0 win in the [[Asian Champions League]] over Saudi Arabian club [[Al Nassr]]. He scored many goals for the club, and provided quality assists to win the Best Striker Award of the 14th Persian Gulf Pro League at the end of the 2014–15 season.

====2015–16====
[[File:Esteghlal Edges Past Persepolis 3-2 to Claim Tehran Derby-37.jpg|thumb|Taremi playing for [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] in [[Tehran derby]].]]
Taremi missed the first week of the new season due to suspension, but in his first game back on 6 August 2015, he scored in a 2–1 loss to [[Esteghlal Khuzestan F.C.|Esteghlal Khuzestan]]. Taremi scored twice in a 2–0 week five win against [[Foolad F.C.|Foolad]]. This was Persepolis' first win of the season and lifted them out of the relegation spot. Taremi's good performances in the month of August earned him the [[Navad]] player of the month as voted by fans.<ref>{{cite web|title=فوتبالی‌ترین {{!}} "طارمی" بهترین بازیکن ماه از نگاه نود شد|url=http://footballitarin.com/link_page.php?id=248567|website=footballitarin.com|access-date=1 September 2015|archive-date=2 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150902130116/http://footballitarin.com/link_page.php?id=248567|url-status=live}}</ref> On 18 December 2015, Taremi scored a brace against [[Rah Ahan F.C.|Rah Ahan]] in Persepolis' 2–0 victory. He ended the first half of the league as top scorer with nine goals in 12 games.

On 4 April 2016, Taremi scored a brace in a 3–2 victory against [[Siah Jamegan Khorasan F.C.|Siah Jamegan]] to keep Persepolis in third place. On 12 April 2016, Taremi was in talks to extend his contract to the end of the 2017–18 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=خبر خوب برای هواداران سرخپوش در آستانه دربی وکیل طارمی|date=13 April 2016 |url=http://www.farsnews.ir/13950124001663|access-date=13 July 2022|archive-date=2 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202011739/http://www.farsnews.ir/13950124001663|url-status=live}}</ref> But eventually, he decided not to renew his contract. On 15 April 2016, Taremi scored a brace in Persepolis' historic 4–2 victory over [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]] in the [[Tehran derby]]. He became the league's top scorer with 16 goals at the end of the season; despite his good performances, his team failed to win the title at the last week.

====2016–17====
Before the start of the new season, Taremi announced that he would not extend his contract, to join to a European team. In July 2016, it was reported that Taremi was linked to [[Süper Lig]] team [[Çaykur Rizespor]]. The move was cancelled after Taremi returned to Iran and signed a two-year contract with [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]].<ref>{{cite web|title=مهدی طارمی با پرسپولیس تمدید کرد|url=http://fararu.com/fa/news/278340|website=Fararu {{!}} فرارو|language=fa-IR|access-date=23 September 2016|archive-date=24 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220924084910/https://fararu.com/fa/news/278340/%D9%85%D9%87%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%BE%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B3-%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%AF%DB%8C%D8%AF-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D8%AF|url-status=live}}</ref> He played his first match for Persepolis in 1–0 win over [[Saipa F.C.|Saipa]], replaced [[Omid Alishah]] in 77th minute. He also scored his first goal of the season in week 4 against [[Saba Qom F.C.|Saba Qom]]. He scored a brace in 3–1 away win over [[Sepahan F.C.|Sepahan]] At the end of the season, the club celebrated its tenth [[Iran Pro League]] title, and Taremi became top scorer for a second consecutive season with 18 goals.

On 8 May 2017, Taremi scored a decisive hat trick against Emirati side [[Al Wahda FC|Al Wahda]] in a 4–2 win to help his team qualify for the Round of 16 of the [[2017 AFC Champions League]]. After his good performances, Taremi was linked with [[Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref>{{cite web|title=دینامو زاگرب کرواسی از برانکو در مورد طارمی اطلاعات گرفت|url=https://www.tarafdari.com/%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%B1/726367/%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%B9%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%86%DB%8C%D9%85%D8%9B-%D8%AF%DB%8C%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B2%D8%A7%DA%AF%D8%B1%D8%A8-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B3%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86%DA%A9%D9%88-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%AF-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA-%DA%AF%D8%B1%D9%81%D8%AA|language=fa|date=15 June 2017|access-date=9 July 2017|archive-date=16 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210916053203/https://www.tarafdari.com/%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%B1/726367/%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%B9%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%86%DB%8C%D9%85%D8%9B-%D8%AF%DB%8C%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B2%D8%A7%DA%AF%D8%B1%D8%A8-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B3%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86%DA%A9%D9%88-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%AF-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA-%DA%AF%D8%B1%D9%81%D8%AA|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2017–18====
Taremi played seven games, scoring on four occasions. During the [[2017–18 Persian Gulf Pro League|2017–18]] season, Taremi was banned for four months because of a contract dispute with Turkish club [[Çaykur Rizespor]] dating back to June 2016, when the player reached an agreement to join the club and later returned to Persepolis. Persepolis were also banned from signing players for two transfer windows. [[FIFA]] ruled in favor of the Turkish club and imposed the ban.<ref>{{cite web|title=Iran's Mehdi Taremi banned for four months by FIFA|url=http://www.tehrantimes.com/news/417019/Iran-s-Mehdi-Taremi-banned-for-four-months-by-FIFA|date=23 September 2017|access-date=9 January 2018|archive-date=10 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180110114701/http://www.tehrantimes.com/news/417019/Iran-s-Mehdi-Taremi-banned-for-four-months-by-FIFA|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Al Gharafa===
[[File:مهدی طارمی.jpg|thumb|Taremi playing for [[Al-Gharafa SC|Al-Gharafa]] in 2018|180px]]
On 8 January 2018, Taremi signed an 18-month contract with the Qatari club [[Al-Gharafa Sports Club|Al-Gharafa]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mehdi Taremi joins Al Gharafa of Qatar|url=http://www.tehrantimes.com/news/420148/Mehdi-Taremi-joins-Al-Gharafa-of-Qatar|website=Tehran Times|date=8 January 2018|access-date=8 January 2018|archive-date=1 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180201183219/http://www.tehrantimes.com/news/420148/Mehdi-Taremi-joins-Al-Gharafa-of-Qatar|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first goal in the first match of [[2018 AFC Champions League group stage|2018 AFC Champions League]] against UAE's [[Al Jazira Club|Al Jazira]]. Taremi first scored goal in Qatar League against [[Al Kharaitiyat SC|Al Kharaitiyat]] on 16 February. On 19 February, he scored a brace against Iranian side [[Tractor Sazi F.C.|Tractor Sazi]] on the second matchday of the AFC Champions League.

=== Rio Ave ===
On 23 July 2019, Taremi signed a two-year contract with [[Football in Portugal|Portuguese football]] club [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.the-afc.com/news/afcsection/taremi-makes-portugal-move|title=Taremi makes Portugal move|website=www.the-afc.com|language=en-GB|access-date=23 July 2019|archive-date=23 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723093051/http://www.the-afc.com/news/afcsection/taremi-makes-portugal-move|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.mehrnews.com/news/147963/Mehdi-Taremi-joins-Portugal-s-Rio-Ave|title=Mehdi Taremi joins Portugal's Rio Ave|date=23 July 2019|website=Mehr News Agency|language=en|access-date=23 July 2019|archive-date=23 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723093052/https://en.mehrnews.com/news/147963/Mehdi-Taremi-joins-Portugal-s-Rio-Ave|url-status=live}}</ref> Taremi scored a hat-trick in his first [[Primeira Liga]] start for the club on 23 August 2019 in a match against [[C.D. Aves|Aves]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvi24.iol.pt/videos-liga/mehdi-taremi/video-o-hat-trick-de-mehdi-no-rio-ave-desp-aves|title=VÍDEO: o hat-trick de Mehdi no Rio Ave-Desp. Aves|website=TVI|date=23 August 2019|access-date=31 January 2020|language=pt|archive-date=23 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823215137/https://tvi24.iol.pt/videos-liga/mehdi-taremi/video-o-hat-trick-de-mehdi-no-rio-ave-desp-aves|url-status=live}}</ref> On 31 August, Taremi won his side three penalties in their match against [[Sporting CP]], all on fouls committed by [[Sebastián Coates]], as Rio Ave won 3–2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/sporting-cp/story/3933309/sporting-defender-concedes-3-penssent-off|title=Sporting defender concedes 3 pens, sent off|publisher=ESPN|date=31 August 2019|access-date=1 September 2019|archive-date=1 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190901194203/https://www.espn.com/soccer/sporting-cp/story/3933309/sporting-defender-concedes-3-penssent-off|url-status=live}}</ref>

Taremi finished his first season with 18 goals, joint top with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] pair [[Pizzi (Portuguese footballer)|Pizzi]] and [[Carlos Vinícius]]; the latter won the official [[Bola de Prata (Portugal)|Bola da Prata]] trophy for playing the fewest minutes of the three.<ref name=":0">{{cite news |title=Mehdi Taremi among Top Three Goalscorers in Primeira Liga |url=https://irannewsdaily.com/2020/07/mehdi-taremi-among-top-three-goalscorers-in-primeira-liga/ |access-date=5 August 2020 |publisher=Iran News Daily |date=26 July 2020 |archive-date=24 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124151653/https://irannewsdaily.com/2020/07/mehdi-taremi-among-top-three-goalscorers-in-primeira-liga/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Porto ===
[[File:Taremi-Por.jpg|thumb|Taremi playing for [[FC Porto|Porto]] in 2021]]
In August 2020, Taremi signed a four-year contract with [[Primeira Liga]] club [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/fc-porto/detalhe/taremi-oficializado-no-fc-porto-conheca-todos-os-detalhes-do-contrato?ref=Record%20mais_2BlocoAreasemDestaques|title=Taremi oficializado no FC Porto: conheça todos os detalhes do contrato|language=pt|newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|date=31 August 2020|access-date=31 August 2020|archive-date=24 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124034004/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/fc-porto/detalhe/taremi-oficializado-no-fc-porto-conheca-todos-os-detalhes-do-contrato?ref=Record%20mais_2BlocoAreasemDestaques|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first league goal for Porto on 8 November 2020 in a 3–1 home win against [[Portimonense S.C.|Portimonense]].<ref>{{cite web |title=The Captain led the Turnaround |url=https://www.fcporto.pt/en/news/20201108-en-the-captain-led-the-turnaround |publisher=FC Porto |date=8 November 2020 |access-date=15 November 2020 |archive-date=16 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201116220516/https://www.fcporto.pt/en/news/20201108-en-the-captain-led-the-turnaround |url-status=live }}</ref> There was a foul on Taremi during the [[2020 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]] in December 2020 which gave Porto a penalty and resulted in their first goal of the match scored by [[Sérgio Oliveira]]. Porto went on to win the 42nd edition of the competition 2–0, which gave Mehdi Taremi his first European medal.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Porto vs. Benfica - 23 December 2020 - Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/12/23/portugal/super-cup/futebol-clube-do-porto/benfica/3331550/|access-date=5 January 2021|website=Soccerway|archive-date=13 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200813081804/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/12/23/portugal/super-cup/futebol-clube-do-porto/benfica/3331550/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 17 February 2021, Taremi opened the scoring for Porto against [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in the round-of-16 first leg in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]]. He became the first Iranian to score in the first knockout phase of the competition.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hafez |first1=Shamoon |title=Porto 2-1 Juventus: Taremi, Marega and Chiesa score as Portuguese side gain advantage |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56039605 |access-date=18 February 2021 |work=BBC Sport |date=17 February 2021 |archive-date=18 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210218031426/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56039605 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 13 April, he scored the game-winning goal with a spectacular bicycle kick in a 1–0 away win over [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in the Champions League quarter-finals, yet his club lost 1–2 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56721849 |title=Chelsea 0–1 FC Porto |website=BBC Sport |date=13 April 2021 |access-date=13 April 2021 |archive-date=13 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210413213619/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56721849 |url-status=live }}</ref> After the [[2021 UEFA Champions League Final|final]], his goal against Chelsea was voted as the best goal of the season's Champions League.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0269-12688f8c6d63-636a2f6dc104-1000--vote-for-goal-of-the-tournament/ |title=Taremi wins Goal of the tournament by fan vote |website=[[UEFA]] |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=4 June 2021 |access-date=4 June 2021 |archive-date=4 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210604231807/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0269-12688f8c6d63-636a2f6dc104-1000--vote-for-goal-of-the-tournament/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The goal also won the "UEFA.com Goal of the Season" award,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/026b-12dea8d6ba9f-2281d9f217f8-1000--taremi-wins-goal-of-the-season/|title=Mehdi Taremi bicycle kick voted UEFA.com Goal of the Season|website=[[UEFA]]|publisher=Union of European Football Associations|date=29 July 2021|access-date=29 July 2021|archive-date=29 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210729110147/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/026b-12dea8d6ba9f-2281d9f217f8-1000--taremi-wins-goal-of-the-season/|url-status=live}}</ref> and was later nominated for the [[FIFA Puskás Award]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/media-releases/the-best-2021-fifa-puskas-award-11-announced|title=FIFA Puskás Award: 11 best goals announced|work=FIFA|access-date=30 November 2021|archive-date=22 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211222142015/https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/media-releases/the-best-2021-fifa-puskas-award-11-announced|url-status=live}}</ref> Taremi finished the [[2020–21 Primeira Liga|2020–21 season]] with 16 goals and 11 assists. He won his first Primeira Liga title in the [[2021–22 Primeira Liga|2021–22 season]] with Porto. His contributions that season included 20 goals and 13 assists. He was the second-highest goalscorer and the third-highest assist provider that season. On 20 May 2023, he scored all four goals in a 4–2 away victory over [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/video-o-resumo-do-eletrizante-famalicao-2-4-fc-porto-com-poquer-de-taremi |title=VÍDEO: O resumo do eletrizante Famalicão 2-4 FC Porto, com póquer de Taremi |publisher=SAPO Desporto |language=pt |date=20 May 2023 }}</ref>

Taremi finished the [[2022–23 FC Porto season|2022–23 season]] with 22 goals and seven assists in the league, earning the [[Bola de Prata (Portugal)|Bola de Prata]], the top scorer award, and his second [[2022–23 Taça de Portugal|Taça de Portugal]] title with Porto.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=24 June 2023 |title=Taremi joins the Liga Portugal bwin Team of the Year |url=http://www.ligaportugal.pt/en/epocas/20222023/noticias/geral/premios-mensais/11-ano/taremi-escolhido-para-o-11-do-ano-da-liga-portugal-bwin/ |access-date=4 August 2023 |website=Liga Portugal}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=28 May 2023 |title=Taremi becomes Primeira Liga's leading scorer |url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/485206/Taremi-becomes-Primeira-Liga-s-leading-scorer |access-date=4 August 2023 |website=Tehran Times |language=}}</ref> He was also named in the Primeira Liga Team of the Year, making it the fourth consecutive time.<ref>{{cite web |date=24 June 2023 |title=Taremi escolhido para o 11 do ano |trans-title=Taremi makes year's 11 |url=https://rr.sapo.pt/bola-branca/noticia/futebol-nacional/2023/06/24/taremi-escolhido-para-o-11-do-ano/336632/ |access-date=2 August 2023 |publisher=Rádio Renascença |language=pt}}</ref><ref name=":1" />
[[File:Taremi 2024 01.jpg|thumb|Taremi playing for [[Inter Milan]] in 2024|180px]]

On 12 May 2024, he scored a 98th-minute goal in a 2–1 victory against [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]], marking his final appearance for Porto at [[Estádio do Dragão]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Hesabi |first=Farrokh |url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/498427/Mehdi-Taremi-bids-farewell-to-Porto-with-tears-and-brilliance |title=Mehdi Taremi bids farewell to Porto with tears and brilliance |publisher=Tehran Times |date=13 May 2024 }}</ref> Later that month, on 26 May, he scored a penalty in extra time, securing a 2–1 victory over Sporting CP in the [[2024 Taça de Portugal final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/3900-porto-beat-10-man-sporting-in-extra-time-to-win-portuguese-cup |title=Porto beat 10-man Sporting in extra time to win Portuguese Cup |publisher=PortuGOAL |date=26 May 2024 }}</ref>

===Inter Milan===
On 13 July 2024, Taremi signed a three-year contract with Italian champions [[Inter Milan]], valid until 30 June 2027. Taremi thus became the first Iranian player as well as the second Asian player in Inter Milan's history, following [[Yūto Nagatomo]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.inter.it/en/news/mehdi-taremi-joins-inter |title=Mehdi Taremi joins Inter {{!}} Inter.it |publisher=Inter Milan |date=13 July 2024 |access-date=16 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Satrio |first=Cornel Dimas |title=Diam-diam Zielinski dan Taremi Tes Medis di Inter Milan, Nerazzurri Rekrut Pemain Terbaik Gratisan |trans-title=Zielinski and Taremi secretly undergo medical tests at Inter Milan, the Nerazzurri recruit the best players for free. |url=https://kaltara.tribunnews.com/2024/02/13/diam-diam-zielinski-dan-taremi-tes-medis-di-inter-milan-nerazzurri-rekrut-pemain-terbaik-gratisan?page=all |access-date=18 July 2024 |website=Tribun Kaltara |language=id}}</ref> On 1 October, he scored his first goal and provided two assists in a 4–0 victory over [[Red Star Belgrade]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.inter.it/en/news/interview-taremi-post-inter-Crvena-zvezda |title=Taremi, the first goal is unforgettable: "It was amazing, I fight every day for this" |publisher=Inter Milan |date=1 October 2024 }}</ref> On 26 January 2025, he netted his first Serie A goal in a 4–0 away win over [[U.S. Lecce|Lecce]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.in/football/report/_/gameId/712330 |title=Inter Milan keep pace with Napoli in 4-goal Lecce rout |publisher=ESPN |date=26 January 2025 }}</ref>

On 6 May 2025, Taremi provided the decisive assist to [[Davide Frattesi]] in the 99th minute of extra time, securing Inter Milan's dramatic victory over [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in the second leg of the Champions League semi-final. With this contribution, he became the second Iranian player in history to reach the Champions League final, following legendary striker [[Ali Daei]] in 1999.<ref>{{cite web |last=Vrakela |first=Marko |title=Iran Superstar Fights Like A 'Gladiator' In Inter Milan 4–3 Barcelona Champions League Drama |url=https://sempreinter.com/2025/05/07/mehdi-taremi-fights-like-gladiator-inter-milan-barcelona-win/ |website=SempreInter.com |date=7 May 2025 |access-date=8 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mehdi Taremi Becomes Second Iranian to Reach Champions League Final |url=https://iranwire.com/en/sports/140986-mehdi-taremi-becomes-second-iranian-to-reach-champions-league-final/ |website=IranWire |access-date=8 May 2025}}</ref>

In July 2025, [[Botafogo]] presented a proposal for a two-and-a-half-year contract for Mehdi Taremi, then at Internazionale.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-25 |title=Proposta do Botafogo por Mehdi Taremi é por contrato de dois anos e meio; atacante pretende seguir na Europa |url=https://fogonarede.com.br/proposta-do-botafogo-por-mehdi-taremi-e-por-contrato-de-dois-anos-e-meio-atacante-pretende-seguir-na-europa/ |access-date=2025-07-26 |website=Fogo na Rede |language=pt-br}}</ref> Taremi refused the offer in order to negotiate with [[Premier League]] clubs.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-25 |title=Medhi Taremi recusa proposta do Botafogo e negocia com equipes da Premier League |url=https://fogonarede.com.br/medhi-taremi-recusa-proposta-do-botafogo-e-negocia-com-equipes-da-premier-league/ |access-date=2025-07-26 |website=Fogo na Rede |language=pt-br}}</ref>

=== Olympiacos ===
On 30 August 2025, it was revealed that Taremi would join [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] for a fee of €2.5 million.<ref>{{Cite web |last=ΧΡΙΣΤΟΦΙΔΕΛΛΗΣ |first=ΔΗΜΗΤΡΗΣ |date=2025-08-30 |title=Ολυμπιακός, μεταγραφές: Έκλεισαν τον Ταρεμί οι ερυθρόλευκοι |url=https://www.sport24.gr/football/olimpiakos-metagrafes-kleinoun-ton-taremi-oi-erithrolefkoi/ |access-date=2025-08-30 |website=SPORT24 |language=el}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-08-30 |title=Έκλεισε Ταρεμί ο Ολυμπιακός! |url=https://www.sportal.gr/podosfairo/article/olympiakos-taremi-ekleise-i-metagrafi-toy-iranoy-for-2025083010452086500 |access-date=2025-08-30 |website=Sportal.gr |language=el}}</ref> A day later, he was announced by the team.<ref>{{Cite web |last=ΧΡΙΣΤΟΦΙΔΕΛΛΗΣ |first=ΔΗΜΗΤΡΗΣ |date=2025-08-31 |title=Ολυμπιακός, μεταγραφές: Ανακοινώθηκε ο Ταρέμι |url=https://www.sport24.gr/football/olimpiakos-metagrafes-anakoinothike-o-taremi/ |access-date=2025-08-31 |website=SPORT24 |language=el}}</ref>

In his [[2025–26 Super League Greece|Super League]] debut against [[Panserraikos F.C.|Panserraikos]] on 13 September, he scored a brace.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-13 |title=Σόου Ποντένσε - Ταρέμι, ερυθρόλευκο τάληρο και τώρα Champions League |url=https://www.sportal.gr/podosfairo/article/olympiakos-panserraikos-5-0-kai-tora-champions-league-2025091315584345782 |access-date=2025-09-13 |website=Sportal.gr |language=el}}</ref> In his [[2025–26 Greek Football Cup|Greek Cup]] debut against [[Asteras Tripolis F.C.|Asteras Tripolis]], he also scored a brace.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-24 |title=Αστέρας Τρίπολης – Ολυμπιακός 1-2: Ταρέμι, σκουπίστε, τελειώσατε! {{!}} Gazzetta |url=https://www.gazzetta.gr/football/kypello-elladas/2476779/asteras-tripolis-olympiakos-1-2-taremi-skoypiste-teleiosate |access-date=2025-09-26 |website=www.gazzetta.gr |language=el}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Taremi played for Iran student's national football team in Turkey tournament and scored 9 goals for the team. He was called up by [[Alireza Mansourian]] to participate in the team's training camp in [[Kish, Iran|Kish Island]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=دو بازیکن پرسپولیس در تیم ملی زیر 22 سال|url=http://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/366974|language=fa-IR|access-date=29 May 2014|archive-date=12 May 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512184005/http://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/366974|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Senior===
[[File:2018 FIFA World Cup Group B march IRN-MAR 28.jpg|thumb|Taremi celebrating Iran's goal against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]
[[File:China-Iran 2019 AFC Asian Cup by Mehdi Zare 12.jpg|thumb|Taremi celebrating his goal against [[China national football team|China]] in [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]]]]
Taremi made his debut against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] in a friendly match on 11 June 2015. He also came on as a second-half substitute in a World Cup Qualifying match against [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]] on 16 June 2015.

On 3 September 2015, Taremi scored his first senior goals, a brace, in a 6–0 victory over [[Guam national football team|Guam]] in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|2018 FIFA World Cup qualifier]].<ref>{{cite web|title=WORLD CUP QUALIFYING – AFC|url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/statistics/id/433438/statistics.html|publisher=[[ESPN FC]]|access-date=3 September 2015|archive-date=2 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150902214154/http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/statistics/id/433438/statistics.html|url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 March 2017, Taremi scored the winning and only goal in Iran's victory against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] in the final round of World Cup qualifying. He followed this up with another goal on 28 March 2017, in a 1–0 victory against [[China national football team|China]]. On 12 June 2017, Taremi scored the second goal for Iran in a 2–0 win over [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] to seal the country's first consecutive qualification to two World Cups.<ref>{{cite web|title=World Cup 2018: Iran join Brazil in qualifying for next year's tournament|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40258091|website=BBC Sport|date=13 June 2017|access-date=14 February 2018|archive-date=29 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171129020921/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40258091|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2018, he was named in Iran's final 23-man [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#Iran|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Iran World Cup 2018 squad and team guide | work = The Telegraph | date = 10 June 2018 | access-date = 11 June 2018 | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/0/iran-world-cup-2018-squad-team-guide/ | archive-date = 10 June 2018 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180610125141/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/0/iran-world-cup-2018-squad-team-guide/ | url-status = live }}</ref> With the score tied 1–1 in stoppage time in Iran's group stage match with Portugal, Taremi missed a point-blank shot wide left that would have eliminated Portugal and advanced Iran to the round of 16.

He was also named in Iran's final 26-man squad by [[Carlos Queiroz]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]. In the first group stage game, he scored two goals as Iran lost 6–2 to [[England national football team|England]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Saka scores twice as England thrash Iran in opener |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63603382 |access-date=21 February 2024 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On March 25, 2025, Taremi scored twice against Uzbekistan in a 2–2 draw, a result that secured Iran's qualification for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], marking their seventh appearance in the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iran qualify for 2026 World Cup despite visa issues |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/mar/25/iran-world-cup-2026-visa-issues |website=The Guardian |date=25 March 2025 |access-date=8 May 2025}}</ref> Later that year, on 8 September, he made his 100th international appearance in a 1–0 defeat against Uzbekistan in the [[2025 CAFA Nations Cup|CAFA Nations Cup]] final.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/517758/Mehdi-Taremi-joins-FIFA-Century-Club |title=Mehdi Taremi joins FIFA Century Club |publisher=Tehran Times |date=12 September 2025 }}</ref>

==Personal life==
He was in a relationship with Iranian actress [[Sahar Ghoreishi]] for months in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://donya-e-eqtesad.com/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4-%D8%B3%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%AA-%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86-62/3639176-%D8%A8%D8%A8%DB%8C%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D8%B8%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%86%D8%B8%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%87-%D9%85%D9%87%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%87-%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B4-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D8%B3%D8%AD%D8%B1-%D9%82%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%B4%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%AF%DB%8C%D9%85-%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%B4%D8%AF |title=اظهارنظر تازه مهدی طارمی درباره رابطه‌اش با سحر قریشی: دوست بودیم و تمام شد |access-date=31 March 2020 |archive-date=24 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220924084943/https://donya-e-eqtesad.com/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4-%D8%B3%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%AA-%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86-62/3639176-%D8%A8%D8%A8%DB%8C%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D8%B8%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%86%D8%B8%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%87-%D9%85%D9%87%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%87-%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B4-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D8%B3%D8%AD%D8%B1-%D9%82%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%B4%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%AF%DB%8C%D9%85-%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%B4%D8%AF |url-status=live }}</ref> In March 2020, Taremi announced that he had started a new relationship and is preparing for marriage.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1675690/%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%DB%8C%DA%A9-%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%87-%D8%AC%D8%AF%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D9%88-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%81%DA%A9%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D8%B2%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AC-%D9%87%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%85 |title=طارمی: در یک رابطه جدید و به فکر ازدواج هستم! |access-date=31 March 2020 |archive-date=24 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220924084921/https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1675690/%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%DB%8C%DA%A9-%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%87-%D8%AC%D8%AF%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D9%88-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%81%DA%A9%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D8%B2%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AC-%D9%87%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%85 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 15 April 2022, [[Sporting CP]], a rival of Taremi's then-club Porto, published an article on their club website and referred to Taremi as "a true snake charmer, someone from Persia always ready to go and perform circus tricks". The article was criticized by Porto fans and Iranians, including the Iranian Ambassador to Portugal, Morteza Damanpak. The club later deleted the article.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:Iranian ambassador’s reaction to Sporting CP’s insult against Taremi|url=https://en.isna.ir/news/1401012816641/Iranian-ambassador-s-reaction-to-Sporting-CP-s-insult-against|publisher=Iranian Students News Agency|accessdate=17 April 2022|language=English|date=17 April 2022|archive-date=18 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220418101244/https://en.isna.ir/news/1401012816641/Iranian-ambassador-s-reaction-to-Sporting-CP-s-insult-against|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Political views ===
Taremi was a supporter of the [[government of the Islamic Republic of Iran]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sinaiee |first=Maryam |date=2025-03-29 |title=Why are Iranians turning away from their national football team? |url=https://www.iranintl.com/en/202503271021 |access-date=2025-11-25 |website=[[Iran International]] |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":3" /> In June 2017, after President [[Hassan Rouhani]] congratulated the national team for qualifying for the 2018 World Cup, Taremi donated his shirt to Rouhani.<ref>{{Cite web|title=مهدی طارمی پیراهنش را به رئیس جمهور اهدا کرد|url=https://www.asriran.com/fa/news/544044/%D9%85%D9%87%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C-%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%86%D8%B4-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B1%D8%A6%DB%8C%D8%B3-%D8%AC%D9%85%D9%87%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D8%AF-%D8%B9%DA%A9%D8%B3|website=Asr Iran|date=June 2017|access-date=2025-11-27|language=Persian}}</ref> On 8 December 2017, Taremi tweeted a message that called for the destruction of [[Israel]] accompanied by a portrait of [[Supreme Leader of Iran|Supreme Leader]] [[Ali Khamenei]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Is Manchester United Seeking an Iranian Player Who Calls for Israel's Destruction? |url=https://iranwire.com/en/sports/122359-is-manchester-united-seeking-an-iranian-player-who-calls-for-israels-destruction/ |access-date=2025-11-25 |website=[[IranWire]] |language=en}}</ref> Many Israelis urged FIFA to ban Taremi from the 2018 World Cup for violating [[FIFA]]'s hate speech policy, with [[Israeli Foreign Ministry]] spokesperson Emmanuel Nachshon also condemning the tweet.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=Fans urge FIFA to ban Iranian player over anti-Israel tweet |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/fans-urge-fifa-to-ban-iranian-player-over-anti-israel-tweet/amp/ |access-date=25 November 2025 |website=Times of Israel}}</ref> Taremi subsequently deleted the tweet, although he did not apologize.<ref name=":2" /> In 2022, ''[[IranWire]]'' reported that Taremi had "a close relationship" with President [[Ebrahim Raisi]].<ref name=":3" /> However, at the end of the same year, the player publicly criticized the [[Mahsa Amini protests|repression of the civil protests]] prompted by the killing of [[Mahsa Amini]]; in the following years, he opposed more and more frequently to the Iranian government's repressive strategies.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |last=Moggia |first=Valerio |date=3 March 2026 |title=La falsa notizia del calciatore Taremi pronto a partire in guerra per difendere l'Iran ha fatto il giro della stampa italiana |url=https://www.facta.news/articoli/falsa-notizia-calciatore-taremi-guerra-stampa-italiana |access-date=6 March 2026 |website=Facta |language=it}}</ref>

On 10 January 2026, Taremi refused to celebrate a goal he scored with Olympiacos during the [[Greek Super Cup]], as a sign of protest towards the [[2026 Iran massacres|mass killing of protesters]] during the civil unrest in Iran.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 January 2026 |title=مهدی طارمی پس از گلزنی در یونان: کنار مردم ایران هستم و نمی‌توانم گل‌هایم را جشن بگیرم |url=https://www.iranintl.com/fa/202601100370 |access-date=6 March 2026 |website=[[Iran International]] |language=fa}}</ref> Later the same month, a fake post shared on [[Facebook]] and [[X (social network)|X]] claiming that Taremi had requested the club to return to Iran in order to fight in the [[2026 Iran war|armed conflict]] was erroneously reported on by various Italian and international media outlets;<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":5">{{Cite web |date=3 March 2026 |title=No, il calciatore iraniano Mehdi Taremi non smetterà di giocare per andare in guerra con l'Iran |url=https://www.ilpost.it/flashes/taremi-guerra-iran-notizia-falsa/ |access-date=6 March 2026 |website=[[Il Post]] |language=it}}</ref> the claim was later dismissed both by the striker's agent, [[Federico Pastorello]],<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":5" /> and the president of Olympiacos, Kostas Karapapas.<ref name=":4" />

